  "body": "### Description of the Issue\r\n\r\nWhen trying to send a pre-filled tx using Metamask, if you do not expand the \"Advanced\" section first, the data field is left empty.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nOn the Ropsten testnet go to the pre-filled page, for instance:\r\n\r\n[MyCrypto Pre-Filled](https://www.mycrypto.com/account/send?&to=0xfEfFcEeF3E7B13aAC3a916647BD75071f96b7B3a&value=0.1&data=0xba298494000000000000000000000000feffceef3e7b13aac3a916647bd75071f96b7b3a&gasLimit=200000)\r\n\r\nSelect \"Metamask\". When new window loads do not expand the \"Advanced\" section. If you press \"Send Transaction\" your tx will be sent with empty data field (it will fail). If you press \"Send transaction\", then \"Cancel\" and then expand the \"Advanced\" section, the fields \"To Address\", \"Amount\" and \"Nonce\" becomes empty.\r\n\r\nIf you want to make it work, firstly you need to expand the \"Advanced\" section and only then press \"Send Transaction\". I think that makes some inconveniences, especially for inexperienced users.\r\n\r\n(I have only tested it with Metamask, not sure if this issue also appears by using other methods).\r\n\r\n### Description of Your Machine\r\n\r\nGoogle Chrome (version: 68.0.3440.106), Windows 10, ASUS laptop\r\n",
